item.description:
Increasing Array lower_bound() returns value that is greater than or equal to x;
upper_bound() returns value strictly greater than x;
Decreasing array: lower_bound() returns value that is less than or equal to x;
upper_bound() retruns value that is strictly less than x;

It is an online sorting algorithm aimed to create piles of cards in such a way that piles are in increasing order down wards.
It can be used to find LIS in O(NlogN) time. Can also be used to find (minimum)number of distinct LIS.
VII dp; for(int i=arr.size()-1;i&gt;=0;--i) { int x=arr[i]; auto it=upper_bound(all(dp),x); if(it==dp.end()) dp.pb(x); else *it=x; } cout&lt;&lt;dp.size();
